&lt;p>I created a vertex paintable material for Eris Online to allow artists to add surface detailing on dungeon floors.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Directional Decal Shader for Environmental Blending In Unity</title><link>https://cathyshih.com/en/work/unity-urp-decal-shader/</link><pubDate>Thu, 12 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://cathyshih.com/en/work/unity-urp-decal-shader/</guid><description>&lt;p>When working with assets in Unity projects, I often find that props can feel &amp;ldquo;out of place&amp;rdquo; in the environment. To address this, I created a custom decal shader that helps blend props more naturally into the scene.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Vertex Blend Triplanar Shader In Unity</title><link>https://cathyshih.com/en/work/unity-urp-vertex-blend-triplanar-shader/</link><pubDate>Fri, 12 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://cathyshih.com/en/work/unity-urp-vertex-blend-triplanar-shader/</guid><description>&lt;p>When I first started using Unity, I was not satisfied with how terrain textures were blended together. Therefore I put together a vertex blend triplanar shader for Unity URP. It blends multiple textures using vertex colors from meshes, which allows us to bake splat maps onto meshes for direct texture application.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Anisotropic Highlight Hair Shader In Unity</title><link>https://cathyshih.com/en/work/unity-urp-anisohighlight-hair-shader/</link><pubDate>Sat, 20 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://cathyshih.com/en/work/unity-urp-anisohighlight-hair-shader/</guid><description>&lt;img
